notes.text: Security update for webkit2gtk3
notes.title: Title of the patch

notes.text:
This update for webkit2gtk3 to version 2.24.2 fixes the following issues:

Security issues fixed:

- CVE-2019-6237, CVE-2019-8571, CVE-2019-8583, CVE-2019-8584, CVE-2019-8586,
  CVE-2019-8587, CVE-2019-8594, CVE-2019-8595, CVE-2019-8596, CVE-2019-8597,
  CVE-2019-8601, CVE-2019-8607, CVE-2019-8608, CVE-2019-8609, CVE-2019-8610,
  CVE-2019-8615, CVE-2019-8611, CVE-2019-8619, CVE-2019-8622, CVE-2019-8623 (bsc#1135715).

This update was imported from the SUSE:SLE-15:Update update project.

notes.text: Multiple memory corruption issues were addressed with improved memory handling. This issue is fixed in iOS 12.3, macOS Mojave 10.14.5, tvOS 12.3, Safari 12.1.1, iTunes for Windows 12.9.5, iCloud for Windows 7.12. Processing maliciously crafted web content may lead to arbitrary code execution.
